<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
No I don't think there are.<P>However, pets do give you a degree of protection from stealthers, more acting as a deterrent. If the pet is on 'defensive' and the stealther attacks you, the pet will immediately attack the stealther. This prevents them re-stealthing, which is really what they are concerned about. At that point quickcast lifetap to get some health back and sit down to stop the poison killing you. Since you were standing next to a few tanks (well you should have been) the stealther should have been hacked apart.<P>In my experience the best defence against stealthers is to not look like a good target. This includes -<BR> - Standing near another cloth caster without a pet. The stealther should go for the lower hanging fruit...<BR> - Stay near your tanks.<BR> - Don't sit down unless you absolutely have to, and stay in combat mode as much as you can.<BR> - Keep moving around.<BR> - Have a pet in tow.<BR> - Look around at where stealthers are likely to be and stay away if possible.<BR> - Pay attention to the chat channel for information on the locations of enemy stealthers.<P>And expect them to get you sometimes. Be prepared and make sure you know a rezzer near by... you're going to need them.<P>--------------------<P>Yosarian<BR>Sorcerer lvl 40<BR>Dragon's Shadow Guild - Nimue
</FONT>
