<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
That is the way it's supposed to work I believe.  I've seen lots of different opinions on the matter, and posted a few times for clarification myself.  I've never seen any official word from Mythic about the different pet modes, but having levelled a sorc to 50 I can offer my observations...<P>Aggressive - Pets will not go on killing sprees as the name would imply.  In aggressive mode, pets will attack anything that attacks them.  Pets will NOT attack anything that attacks you.  Pets will attack anything you target and then click the "Attack" button.  Pets will, ON THEIR OWN, attack any mob they have aggressive faction with!  <P>Defensive - In defensive mode, pets will attack anything that attacks you.  Pets will attack anything that attacks them.  Pets will attack anything you target and then click the "Attack" button.<P>Passive - In passive mode, pets will not attack anything.  Even clicking the "Attack" button, the pet will not attack your target.  Selecting passive mode for your pet is also the only way I've found to clear your pet's agro list.<P><BR>Other observations about pet behavior... <P>- I'm not entirely sure about this one, but once you tell your pet to attack a target, it will continue to attack other PCs in the same group or other linked mobs.  Not sure if this is the case in Aggressive, Defensive, or both.<P>- The "Go To Targ." function doesn't work on a pet in passive mode for some reason.<P>- To make a pet enter a keep with you, port into the keep via the gatekeeper, once inside, target a player or object inside the keep and click "Go To Target".<P>- Once a pet has gotten a certain distance away from you, the pet window will appear to "freeze" and no longer update.  The buttons still work, but the graphics will no longer update.  You can correct this by releasing the pet, quickly mezzing, then re-charming.<P><BR>Personally, I usually have my pet on aggressive.  This allows me to QC mez a mob or PC that attacks me, without having to worry about the pet breaking that mez.  Even after the 1.50 pet/mez change I still prefer Aggressive because I don't trust the pet to not break mez.  I've noticed that once a pet starts attacking something, it will not stop attacking until you set it to passive, even after you've mezzed it.  The bad thing about aggressive is what I mentioned about the pet attacking other mobs that it hates.  This is something you have to be extremely careful about in the frontiers.  For example, if you charm a Loghery man and run through the Grogan camp, you are going to have a mess on your hands!<P>Let me know if I'm wrong about any of this.  I'll add more stuff as I remember it!  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Admin - Level 50 Sorcerer - Kay<BR>Breeto - Level 47 Armsman - Kay
</FONT>
